The paper proposes a distributed, flexible nonlinear tensor factorization model that can effectively avoid expensive computations and structural restrictions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of variational evidence lower bound (ELBO) and inference algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also discusses the application of the proposed method in Click-Through-Rate (CTR) prediction for online advertising, which falls under the data mining (cs.DM) sub-category.
